Running Python code interactively: import pandas as pd

# Load the CSV file
data = pd.read_csv('/workspace/april-attendance-data.csv')

# Convert 'Arrival Time' to datetime
data['Arrival Time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Arrival Time'], format='%H:%M:%S')

# Define the late arrival time
late_time = pd.to_datetime('10:00:00', format='%H:%M:%S')

# Filter late arrivals
data['Late Arrival'] = data['Arrival Time'] > late_time

# Count late arrivals per employee
late_arrivals_count = data[data['Late Arrival']].groupby('Employee Name').size()

# Get the top 5 employees with the most late arrivals
top_late_arrivals = late_arrivals_count.nlargest(5)
